Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer: Full Stack* with *Thatch*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production web applications across the full stack — from React user interfaces to FastAPI and Spring Boot backend services — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and end-to-end ownership this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built a full-stack React and TypeScript visual workflow platform backed by FastAPI — giving users end-to-end control of complex product surfaces while Temporal handled durable, resumable execution of complex business logic at scale. Alongside it, I engineered a multi-agent CRM platform in Python, LangGraph, and FastAPI serving 10,000+ users with tenant-aware access control, and a FastMCP server exposing 160+ backend actions to partner-facing workflows — with OpenTelemetry instrumentation providing the production reliability, debugging visibility, and continuous improvement feedback loops that real operational systems require. I also built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with trace-based evals that gate every deploy against correctness, code quality, and system design standards, and LlamaIndex-powered RAG agents that streamlined partner onboarding. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot backed by PostgreSQL and Redis — a production system with direct operational and financial impact handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO — and orchestrated long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions to achieve production reliability across 100K+ weekly executions. These roles have prepared me to take ownership of meaningful product areas from concept to production and contribute across the stack to what Thatch is building.

My academic research has given me a rigorous foundation in distributed systems design and complex system orchestration — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative, high-empathy culture Thatch values. I built a distributed coding-agent orchestrator (Dark Factory) that decomposes complex requests into dependency-aware task DAGs and executes them across multi-machine agents with retries and timeout handling — end-to-end ownership of a complex production system built for correctness and long-term maintainability, not just speed.

I have always been passionate about building software that puts real people in control of their own experience and making complex, high-stakes systems feel simple and trustworthy. Thatch's mission to build a healthcare system people love — one centered on giving individuals genuine control over their own benefits — is exactly the kind of work I want to pour my energy into. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

